Lack of enough sleep can cause many health problems, including cardiovascular problems, cancer, breast cancer, increased mortality, and increase sensitivity to pain.
Getting enough sleep helps memory, coordination and overall better mental and physical performance.
Sleep disorders and lack of enough sleep affect all ages including children.
Taking short naps during the early afternoon does help but is mostly not accepted in U.S.A.
Adults should get between 7 to 9 hours sleep each day, more for young adults and children.
Getting a good night’s sleep has its rewards, such as reduced fatigue and better concentration, many studies have shown.
